Two girls and a boy fleeing from their aunt Jennifer Silas in Benue State have been found in Anambra State. The siblings Miracle Darlington, 13, Delight Darlington, 8, and Goodness Darlington, 10, who hail from Imo State, reportedly lived with their aunt in Ekporo community in Benue State after their parents passed away. They told police after being found wandering in Ezira town in Orumba South Local Government Area of Anambra State that they fled Benue because their aunty was maltreating them. Police spokesman Haruna Mohammed who confirmed the incident, said the victims were found wandering in Ezira community. He said the children were in protective custody of the Umunze Divisional anti human trafficking unit, while investigation had begun to ascertain circumstances surrounding their predicament.